<dl id="n40047b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40047b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40047b"> 47(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> deil</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;The devil was always and literally at hand <font color="green">[in Scotland]</font>,&rdquo; says Buckle, &ldquo;he was haunting them, speaking to them, and tempting them. Go where they would he was there.&rdquo; <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
